<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-09-04T13:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-09-04T13:35:00-05:00" n="585" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d585">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Standard Oil/30: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-04T22:00:00+03:25"><hi rend="italic">September 4,
                                        1921—10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received September 7—10:15
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>52. British Minister tells me confidentially that his Government has
                            instructed him to protest against Russian oil concessions being
                            transferred to American concern.</p>
                        <p>I am also informed that French interests are seeking the same
                            concessions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>